{
  "texts": [
    "Given the over-parameterized nature of these networks, a large number of samples is required for the adaptation of these models for clinical genomics applications.",
    "Furthermore, within the current framework of these models, explicit encoding of known technical variation (e.g.",
    "batch) is necessary, thus limiting the generalizability to new datasets.",
    "To overcome these challenges, we developed Orion, a two-arm semi-supervised multi-input variational auto-encoder for a liquid biopsy application using oncRNAs.",
    "We showcase the capability of Orion in learning a generalizable pattern of oncRNAs for a variety of applications, including early detection of lung cancer and removing batch effects in the presence of confounded signals."
  ]
}